{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T15:10:02.263459310Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-1397bf9d","body":"Add a test for `br ready` failure (e.g., br binary not found or timeout during the ready query). The code at lines 505-518 of `src/cli/run.rs` correctly transitions to `NeedsOperator` when `request_ready_milestone_beads` returns `Err`, but no test exercises this path. All four existing tests cover bv failure or successful br queries, leaving the br-failure → NeedsOperator branch untested.","dedup_key":"9b346b943cfdf6d4fd573662b6a42d69aa2e1822f4dc286a5b13f1cf5b31bd06","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":18,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T15:10:02.272454495Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-661460da","body":"Remove the unnecessary `async` qualifier from `transition_controller_for_selection_outcome` (line 448 of `src/cli/run.rs`). The function contains no `.await` calls — it only calls the synchronous `sync_controller_state`. Making it `async` forces every caller to `.await` a future that resolves immediately, adding unnecessary overhead.","dedup_key":"e275d9da211529bf51481ff337264fd8cee4daeec6053ec826ab98893ce5ecd9","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":19,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T15:10:02.281517929Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-7714406a","body":"Wire the new selector into a real controller path before approving this bead. `select_next_milestone_bead` is implemented at `src/cli/run.rs:470`, but there are no production call sites; the only references are the new unit tests at `src/cli/run.rs:1873`, `src/cli/run.rs:1921`, `src/cli/run.rs:1961`, and `src/cli/run.rs:1994`. At the same time, successful reconciliation still moves the controller back to `Selecting` at `src/cli/run.rs:1030`, while the start/resume paths continue to only prepare already bead-linked projects at `src/cli/run.rs:1244` and `src/cli/run.rs:1363`. As shipped, the controller never actually asks `bv` for the next bead in production and will stall in `selecting` after a completed bead.","dedup_key":"f4bd6fa6121fbb2d171e0040553c7eaad2c8230d1f9df7e3b6e7a28475e811bf","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":20,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T15:10:02.290396095Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-769c4884","body":"Tighten `br_show_error_is_missing` so only real 'bead not found' exits are treated as missing. The current check at `src/cli/run.rs:313` treats any `BrExitError` containing `unknown` in stdout/stderr as a missing bead, and `request_bead_detail` then converts that into `Ok(None)` at `src/cli/run.rs:366`. That will misclassify real tool failures such as `unknown flag` or `unknown subcommand` as a blocked/missing bead instead of sending the controller to `needs_operator`, which violates the selection policy for `br` failures.","dedup_key":"1dde21ccddfe56c6067d8bc7cd5f1e5f2ac7349ffaed8b8e742f70437f8febb9","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
