{"sequence":37,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T15:40:30.480598529Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-2753335a","body":"Add a test for the code path at run.rs:540-555 where bv recommends a bead that is not part of the milestone plan. This path transitions to Blocked with a reason containing 'not part of milestone', but no test exercises it. A test should create a milestone with known beads, have bv recommend a bead ID outside that set, and assert the controller lands in Blocked with the expected reason message.","dedup_key":"ad4a5ff6aca0a59b403f6dde6509a71c43d49df1bbb8b9705c65110daa60e91d","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":38,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T15:40:30.490280582Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-6b8d6c51","body":"In the NoRecommendation path (run.rs:588-613), when bv reports no actionable bead but br shows ready milestone beads, the controller goes to Blocked. Consider whether this should be NeedsOperator instead, since the discrepancy suggests bv may be misconfigured or out of sync. If the current Blocked behavior is intentional, add a code comment explaining why Blocked is preferred over NeedsOperator for this case, and add a test covering this specific sub-path (bv returns no recommendation, br returns non-empty ready list).","dedup_key":"2c2202ff08a0961abe22aa8e26b036e8c594e6ee2bcc070ad54ccdd98d2b5289","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":39,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T15:40:30.499951494Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-345ae2fe","body":"Wire the new selector into the automation-runtime reconciliation path, not just the CLI post-run helpers. `reconcile_success` still returns non-final milestones to `Selecting` at `src/contexts/automation_runtime/success_reconciliation.rs:384-400`, and the daemon's success path only logs the hint afterward at `src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs:1945-1975`. The new selector is invoked only from the CLI wrappers in `src/cli/run.rs:1405-1418`, `src/cli/run.rs:1542-1555`, and `src/cli/run.rs:1585-1596`, so daemon-driven milestone execution will still stall in `selecting` instead of performing the bv/br validation flow.","dedup_key":"a1dd6004df429c0af11019b3f8f30258937830254548fed661619a6f189c13cd","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":40,"timestamp":"2026-04-08T15:40:30.509729466Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-b3293367","body":"Persist the bv recommendation before the `br ready` validation step. In `src/cli/run.rs:492-517`, a successful `bv --robot-next` result is kept only in memory; if `br ready` then times out or fails, the controller moves to `needs_operator` with a reason that no longer mentions which bead bv recommended. That violates the stated selection policy to record the recommendation before claiming and leaves operators without the key audit datum for the failed selection attempt.","dedup_key":"1c9a11683aa7be40490a643f39c2198a91b941e27bb01a9f6edf61c66cfccb20","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260408144314","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
